Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 4/17/00


NAB Update

I have not heard from SeaChange or Phillips directly regarding how the demo
went, but I have talked to several of our people who went to the show.
According to them, everything seemed fine.


ClearCase migration

I finally completed the merged of the dpi and ratemux source trees.  Now all
TI DSP source codes reside in the same parent directory, with the common
files together in one common subdirectory.  We gave this version to IT
and they are helping us to set it up for ClearCase.  We had some discussion
of whether we should put different modules (statmux, demux, kernel) in
different VOBs but after we clarified some misunderstanding we dicided to
put everying of the ratemux project, including the PPC code, into a common
VOB.


DPI Issues

Continue to work on the reliability issues.  Talked with Matt and identified
some long-term issues that DPI has when working together with statmux.
But progress is slow since the lab has not been fully set up. 


